http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/InterContinental-to-operate-51-more-hotels-in-5-years/article14021359.ece

InterContinental Hotels Group (IHG), a global hospitality major, is planning to operate at least 51 hotel properties in India with 10,000 rooms in the next three to five years.“We are planning to open 51 hotels in new cities such as Kolkata, Lucknow and Andhra Pradesh,” said Arindam Kunar, IHG Area General Manager South.“The new projects are in different stages of development-design, planning and construction.”Talking to The Hindu, IHG Head of South West Asia, Shanta de Silva, said during the current year, IHG would open four hotels — three in India and one in Bangladesh.To set up 150 hotelsIn the next 10-15 years, the company is planning to set up at least 150 hotels in IndiaAt present, IHG operates 25 hotels with 4,000 rooms.